HpnicfQinQSwitchState.name: HpnicfQinQSwitchState
HpnicfQinQSwitchState.description: An enumerated value which indicates the state of switch.

hpnicfQinQBpduTunnelSwitch.name: hpnicfQinQBpduTunnelSwitch
hpnicfQinQBpduTunnelSwitch.description: The global configuration switch of BPDU 802.1q tunnel. If global configuration is disabled, BPDU tunnel function will be disabled despite of the corresponding configuration of interface. BPDU tunnel function of a certain interface would work only if the global and interface's switch are both enabled.

hpnicfQinQEthernetTypeValue.name: hpnicfQinQEthernetTypeValue
hpnicfQinQEthernetTypeValue.description: Ethernet protocol type configuring for a global value. The ethernet protocol type is also the TPID(Tag Protocol Identity) field of a VLAN tag described in 802.1q document. This value can be also configured for an individual interface or VLAN. The node that configure this value for a single interface is hpnicfQinQIfEthernetType, whose priority is higher than hpnicfQinQEthernetTypeValue. That means, if the value configured for a interface is different from the global value, the switch will select the configuration of the interface and ignore the global configuration. The ethernet protocol type of node hpnicfQinQVidEthernetType that configured for a VLAN has the highest priority.

hpnicfQinQServiceTPIDValue.name: hpnicfQinQServiceTPIDValue
hpnicfQinQServiceTPIDValue.description: Ethernet protocol type configured for service VLAN tags globally. The ethernet protocol type is also the TPID(Tag Protocol Identity) field of a VLAN tag described in 802.1q document. This value can be also configured for an individual interface. The node that configure this value for a single interface is hpnicfQinQIfServiceTPIDValue, whose priority is higher than hpnicfQinQServiceTPIDValue. That means, if the value configured for a interface is different from the global value, the switch will select the configuration of the interface and ignore the global configuration.

hpnicfQinQCustomerTPIDValue.name: hpnicfQinQCustomerTPIDValue
hpnicfQinQCustomerTPIDValue.description: Ethernet protocol type configured for customer VLAN tags globally. The ethernet protocol type is also the TPID(Tag Protocol Identity) field of a VLAN tag described in 802.1q document. This value can be also configured for an individual interface. The node that configure this value for a single interface is hpnicfQinQIfCustomerTPIDValue, whose priority is higher than hpnicfQinQCustomerTPIDValue. That means, if the value configured for a interface is different from the global value, the switch will select the configuration of the interface and ignore the global configuration.

hpnicfQinQBpduTunnelTable.name: hpnicfQinQBpduTunnelTable
hpnicfQinQBpduTunnelTable.description: A table for configuring 802.1q BPDU tunnel function for interfaces.

hpnicfQinQBpduTunnelEntry.name: hpnicfQinQBpduTunnelEntry
hpnicfQinQBpduTunnelEntry.description: An entry for configuring 802.1q BPDU tunnel function for interfaces.

hpnicfQinQProtocolIndex.name: hpnicfQinQProtocolIndex
hpnicfQinQProtocolIndex.description: The index of protocol on which the BPDU tunnel state will be set. 'bpdu' represents status of BPDU tunnel. 'stp' represents STP tunnel. 'gmosaic' represents GMOSAIC tunnel. 'igmp' represents IGMP tunnel. STP/GMOSAIC/IGMP tunnel will start to work only if BPDU tunnel and STP/GMOSAIC/IGMP tunnel are both enabled.

hpnicfQinQBpduRowStatus.name: hpnicfQinQBpduRowStatus
hpnicfQinQBpduRowStatus.description: Operation status of this table entry.

hpnicfQinQPriorityRemarkTable.name: hpnicfQinQPriorityRemarkTable
hpnicfQinQPriorityRemarkTable.description: A table for configuring priority field in 802.1Q-in-Q outer VLAN tag for interfaces. This feature uses the priority of an inner VLAN tag to remark the priority of an outer VLAN tag.

hpnicfQinQPriorityRemarkEntry.name: hpnicfQinQPriorityRemarkEntry
hpnicfQinQPriorityRemarkEntry.description: An entry for configuring priority remark function for interfaces.

hpnicfQinQPriorityValue.name: hpnicfQinQPriorityValue
hpnicfQinQPriorityValue.description: The priority value in inner VLAN tag. Since the priority range is from 0 to 7, yet the index range is from 1 to 8. Thus, the actual priority value equals to the value that subtracts 1 from corresponding index value.

hpnicfQinQPriorityRemarkValue.name: hpnicfQinQPriorityRemarkValue
hpnicfQinQPriorityRemarkValue.description: The new priority value used to fill outer tag.

hpnicfQinQPriorityRowStatus.name: hpnicfQinQPriorityRowStatus
hpnicfQinQPriorityRowStatus.description: Operation status of this table entry.

hpnicfQinQVidTable.name: hpnicfQinQVidTable
hpnicfQinQVidTable.description: A table for configuring VLAN ID of the 802.1Q-in-Q interfaces.

hpnicfQinQVidEntry.name: hpnicfQinQVidEntry
hpnicfQinQVidEntry.description: An entry for configuring VLAN ID of the 802.1Q-in-Q interfaces.

hpnicfQinQInboundVidListLow.name: hpnicfQinQInboundVidListLow
hpnicfQinQInboundVidListLow.description: The inbound VLAN IDs which need 802.1Q-in-Q processing. The VLAN ID range, described by bitmap, is from 1 to 2048. The length of bitmap is 256 in bytes. Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight VLANs, with the first octet specifying VLANs 1 through 8, the second octet specifying VLANs 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the highest numbered VLAN, and the least significant bit represents the lowest numbered VLAN.

hpnicfQinQInboundVidListHigh.name: hpnicfQinQInboundVidListHigh
hpnicfQinQInboundVidListHigh.description: The inbound VLAN IDs which need 802.1Q-in-Q processing. The VLAN ID range, described by bitmap, is from 2049 to 4094. The length of bitmap is 256 in bytes. Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight VLANs, with the first octet specifying VLANs 2049 through 2056, the second octet specifying VLANs 2057 through 2064, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the highest numbered VLAN, and the least significant bit represents the lowest numbered VLAN.

hpnicfQinQVidEthernetType.name: hpnicfQinQVidEthernetType
hpnicfQinQVidEthernetType.description: Ethernet protocol type configuring for a VLAN.

hpnicfQinQVidRowStatus.name: hpnicfQinQVidRowStatus
hpnicfQinQVidRowStatus.description: Operation status of this table entry.

hpnicfQinQVidSwapTable.name: hpnicfQinQVidSwapTable
hpnicfQinQVidSwapTable.description: A table for configuring 802.1Q-in-Q inner VLAN ID swapping function for interfaces.

hpnicfQinQVidSwapEntry.name: hpnicfQinQVidSwapEntry
hpnicfQinQVidSwapEntry.description: An entry for configuring 802.1Q-in-Q inner VLAN ID swapping function for interfaces.

hpnicfQinQVidSwapOld.name: hpnicfQinQVidSwapOld
hpnicfQinQVidSwapOld.description: The old VLAN ID of original 802.1Q packets.

hpnicfQinQVidSwapNew.name: hpnicfQinQVidSwapNew
hpnicfQinQVidSwapNew.description: The new VLAN ID of original 802.1Q packets.

hpnicfQinQVidSwapRowStatus.name: hpnicfQinQVidSwapRowStatus
hpnicfQinQVidSwapRowStatus.description: Operation status of this table entry.

hpnicfQinQPrioritySwapTable.name: hpnicfQinQPrioritySwapTable
hpnicfQinQPrioritySwapTable.description: A table for configuring 802.1Q-in-Q inner VLAN priority swapping function for interfaces. Using this function, the priority of inner VLAN tag can be modified.

hpnicfQinQPrioritySwapEntry.name: hpnicfQinQPrioritySwapEntry
hpnicfQinQPrioritySwapEntry.description: An entry for configuring 802.1Q-in-Q inner VLAN priority swapping function for interfaces.

hpnicfQinQPrioritySwapOld.name: hpnicfQinQPrioritySwapOld
hpnicfQinQPrioritySwapOld.description: The old priority of original 802.1Q packets. It is the priority of inner VLAN tag. Since the VLAN priority range is from 0 to 7, yet the index range is from 1 to 8. Thus, the actual priority value equals to the value that subtracts 1 from corresponding index value.

hpnicfQinQPrioritySwapNew.name: hpnicfQinQPrioritySwapNew
hpnicfQinQPrioritySwapNew.description: The new priority of original 802.1Q packets. It is the priority of inner VLAN tag after swapped.

hpnicfQinQPrioritySwapRowStatus.name: hpnicfQinQPrioritySwapRowStatus
hpnicfQinQPrioritySwapRowStatus.description: Operation status of this table entry.

hpnicfQinQIfConfigTable.name: hpnicfQinQIfConfigTable
hpnicfQinQIfConfigTable.description: A table for configuring 802.1Q-in-Q functions for interfaces.

hpnicfQinQIfConfigEntry.name: hpnicfQinQIfConfigEntry
hpnicfQinQIfConfigEntry.description: An entry for configuring 802.1Q-in-Q functions for interfaces.

hpnicfQinQIfEthernetType.name: hpnicfQinQIfEthernetType
hpnicfQinQIfEthernetType.description: Ethernet protocol type configuring for an interface.

hpnicfQinQIfSwitch.name: hpnicfQinQIfSwitch
hpnicfQinQIfSwitch.description: Switch of 802.1Q-in-Q functions configuring for an interface.

hpnicfQinQIfRowStatus.name: hpnicfQinQIfRowStatus
hpnicfQinQIfRowStatus.description: Operation status of this table entry.

hpnicfQinQIfServiceTPIDValue.name: hpnicfQinQIfServiceTPIDValue
hpnicfQinQIfServiceTPIDValue.description: Service TPID value configured for an interface.

hpnicfQinQIfCustomerTPIDValue.name: hpnicfQinQIfCustomerTPIDValue
hpnicfQinQIfCustomerTPIDValue.description: Customer TPID value configured for an interface.

hpnicfQinQIfUplinkSwitch.name: hpnicfQinQIfUplinkSwitch
hpnicfQinQIfUplinkSwitch.description: Switch of the uplink 802.1Q-in-Q function for an interface.

hpnicfQinQIfDownlinkSwitch.name: hpnicfQinQIfDownlinkSwitch
hpnicfQinQIfDownlinkSwitch.description: Switch of the downlink 802.1Q-in-Q function for an interface.
